<p>I created an Apache Camel Route for MQTT message transforming from MQTT broker to MongoDB. And I got a "Body is not conversible to type DBObject" error even if the message is already a JSON string for MongoDB.</p>  <p>Now, I used the DBObject class to solve this problem temporarily. But how to routing a MongoDB JSON string message without DBObject in Apache Camel?</p>  <p>The original routing code:</p>  <pre><code>from("mqtt:foo?subscribeTopicName=bar/") .to("mongodb:myDb?database=foo&amp;collection=bar&amp;operation=insert"); </code></pre>  <p>Current solution by DBObject class:</p>  <pre><code>from("mqtt:foo?subscribeTopicName=bar/").process(     new Processor(){         @Override         public void process(Exchange exchange) throws Exception {             String payload = exchange.getIn().getBody(String.class);             DBObject doc=new BasicDBObject();             doc.put("message", payload);             exchange.getIn().setBody(doc, DBObject.class);         }     } ) .to("mongodb:myDb?database=foo&amp;collection=bar&amp;operation=insert"); </code></pre>  <p>Error log:</p>  <pre><code>org.apache.camel.component.mongodb.CamelMongoDbException: MongoDB operation = insert, Body is not conversible to type DBObject nor List&lt;DBObject&gt; </code></pre>